<paragraph id="8BC9064CFFCA6355F7867B1331F448E5" blockId="3.[2058,2651,1826,2252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<taxonomicName id="4C767DCFFFCA6355F7867B13312C487F" authority="Krefft, 1863" authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1863" box="[2063,2411,2105,2134]" class="Mammalia" family="Burramyidae" genus="Cercartetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="nanus" subSpecies="unicolor">C. n. unicolor Krefft, 1863</taxonomicName>
— mainland Australia, from the Queensland/New South Wales border down the E coast through S Victoria to SE South Australia.
